sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant BUS as Bus topics<br/>(AiTriageConfig.topics[])
    participant TRI as Triage Service λ
    participant SIG as Shape Cache<br/>(hash source+type+fields)
    participant REG as Schema Registry<br/>(authoritative contracts)
    participant BUD as AiTriageBudget<br/>(platform-level)
    participant MASK as PII Masker
    participant LLM as Bedrock
    participant VAL as Vocabulary Validator<br/>(typeIds·roles·channels)
    participant MAP as Mapping Store<br/>(origin:ai-triage, shadow)
    participant ADM as Admin / policy
    participant PIPE as Normal Pipeline

    BUS->>TRI: event (from configured topic)
    TRI->>SIG: GET shape-sig = hash(source, detail-type, field-set)
    alt known shape
        SIG-->>TRI: cached decision (rule or ignore)
        Note over TRI: execute cached rule at ZERO model cost<br/>5-14M events/day → ~20-200 model calls/day
        TRI->>PIPE: apply rule (notify or skip)
    else novel shape
        SIG-->>TRI: miss
        TRI->>BUD: check platform AiTriageBudget
        alt over budget
            BUD-->>TRI: denied
            Note over TRI: audit: unclassified — no notification, no guess
        else ok
            TRI->>REG: GET schema + compatibility constraints
            REG-->>TRI: authoritative field types + compatibility
            TRI->>MASK: schema + masked sample events (§10.5 pipeline)
            MASK-->>TRI: PII-free input
            TRI->>LLM: author a BusMapping: notify? whom? channels? fieldMap?
            LLM-->>TRI: JSON BusMapping draft
            TRI->>VAL: validate against existing typeIds + RBAC roles + channels
            alt hallucinated role / unknown typeId
                VAL-->>TRI: rejected
                Note over TRI: audit: validation_failed — never a guess send
            else valid
                VAL-->>TRI: ok
                TRI->>MAP: INSERT origin=ai-triage, status=SHADOW, kill_switch=true
                TRI->>SIG: SET hash → rule (cache for future events)
                Note over MAP: audit: rule_authored{shape, confidence}
                ADM->>MAP: review diff → promote shadow→active
                Note over ADM: or auto-promote if confidence ≥ policy threshold
                MAP->>PIPE: rule now executes deterministically
            end
        end
    end
